FBIS4-55747 "dreeu098_b_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-098 Daily Report 19 May 1994 BULGARIA Berov Cabinet Survives No-Confidence Vote Berov Cabinet Survives No-Confidence Vote AU1905181594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1729 GMT 19 May 94 AU1905181594 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network Bulgarian BFN [Text] [Announcer] At the end of our news and music program "Something More," we have the results of the ballot on the motion of no confidence in the Berov government. Here is our reporter Antoaneta Puncheva: [Puncheva] A total of 96 National Assembly deputies voted in favor of the motion of no confidence in the government [121 votes are required for the motion to succeed]; 25 deputies voted against the motion, and one ballot was declared invalid. These are the results that National Assembly Chairman Aleksandur Yordanov will officially announce from the speaker's platform.
